verse.lines:
I was looking toward the sky,
Wishing that I could fly;
But I was locked up in this old barnyard,
Without even knowing why;
Eating from this rotten food,
That I never learnt to want it;
I stayed here for a long, long time,
Not knowing, who I am,
Who I am?
Who I am?

Loneliness enslaved my soul,
I was troubled and confused;
Coz in my heart there's a deep call,
That I never want to loose;
And how can I ever leave this place,
And meet someone to help me;
And that's the time I heard the Voice,
" You're an Eagle"
